pdf_text: Made by Women. For E veryone . Our Vision At Naario, we‚Äôre reimagining food for the next decade. Building a millet-first ecosystem that delivers on nutrition, climate resilience, and new-age consumer demand. By putting women at the center, we‚Äôre not just creating a business , we‚Äôre shaping a new category that will define the future of food. We‚Äôre bold, we‚Äôre disruptive, and we‚Äôre here to make millets mainstream, with taste and trust leading the way. Sourcing Processing Community/ Habit Building 0 1 0 2 0 3 Sustainability Aspect Millets use 70% less water than rice and grow in dry, low-input soil. They support regenerative farming, reduce carbon intensity, and preserve seed diversity Government and Global Trends 2023 was the International Year of Millets Indian govt is integrating millets into PDS, schools & hospitals. Global food agencies are investing in millet-based innovation and climate strategy Built for Today‚Äôs Health Problems Millets help manage diabetes, PCOS, and gut health without changing what people love to eat. Low GI, gluten-free, high-fiber- easy fit for daily staples. Health, Climate, Policy- All roads lead to Millets! Timing the Shift: What‚Äôs Changing Government interventions like International Year of Millets + millets in midday meals FSSAI mandates encouraging fortification with millet FMCGs acquiring brands like Soulful Google Search for ‚Äúmillets for diabetes‚Äù and ‚Äúragi snacks‚Äù up by 3X in last 2 years . Global ‚Äúancient grains‚Äù market growing at >8% CAGR , millets included. Timing the Shift: Why it Matters Consumers shifting to Low-GI, fiber-rich grains like Ragi, Jowar, Bajra from white rice, maida, sugar Consumers are now eating for gut, sugar, and hormone health (but not giving up taste) They‚Äôve moved on health food= for weight loss only to Family-first wellness ‚Äì same meal for kids, moms, and dadaji They are actively seeking local, trust-based clean food brands They‚Äôre adapting to nani-approved ingredients with modern packaging from insta and gym approved fad Total Market- Millets as Functional Food Source: Grand View Research TAM- 312 Billion (Rs) SAM- 200 Cr (Rs) SOM- 32 Cr (Rs) 2025 2028 Avg no of people consuming millets (Mn) 125 228 AOV (Rs) 200 400 TAM (Bn) 25 91 % Urban 30% 35-40% SAM (Bn Rs) 20-30 SOM (1% Share )(Cr Rs) 32 Naario- Born from the Lives We Aim to Improve Vestibulum congue Trust-based channels Distribution based on recommendations Women Makers + Consumers Millets Functional, Local, Habit Forming Naario ‚óè Products made by women, for women and families ‚óè Built on everyday habits, not hype ‚óè Powered by community Built to Serve the Women who shape what India eats Moms | 30-45 Top picks: Millets Attas, Porridge Moms | 30-45 Top picks: Muesli for rushed mornings Young Millennials | 25-35 Top picks: Muesli,, Snack Bhakhri We‚Äôre not just selling food ‚Äî we‚Äôre shaping everyday habits of the modern Indian woman.
